            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " help, but there are thieves who are determined to get past those kinds of barriers. Then there are these outlaws in the Dallas-Fort Worth area of Texas who have been using unmarked tow trucks to ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "snag three Chevrolet Camaros",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/stolen-camaro-recovered-in-kansas-field/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " in late September.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/10/Motorious--31.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Twitter"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Police in Mansfield have released images taken from cameras in the area of the thefts. They show two ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "tow trucks",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/stolen-1969-firebird/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", one a white Ram and the other a black Chevrolet Silverado with roof lights stealing the Camaros. According to police, this isn’t a case of repo guys taking cars people haven’t paid for, before anyone draws that conclusion and dismisses this case.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The three Camaros which were stolen were later recovered. However, the result was anything but happy. The engine and transmission had been yanked out of all three, then they were dumped within a one-mile radius. That lone would seem to indicate these two tow trucks are working together.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/10/Motorious---2--17.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Twitter"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Police not only posted the photos of the tow trucks on Twitter, which admittedly aren’t the best quality, they also put up a video of the Ram tow truck driving slowly by a first-gen Camaro. The muscle car is parked in a well-lit area, so it’s a pretty brazen crime. We wouldn’t be surprised if these guys will keep going after other performance cars if they aren’t caught.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/MansfieldPDTX/status/1313920415589380097",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Here is video of the suspect’s white Dodge Tow Truck. If you recognize it, please contact Lieutenant Harrell at 817-804-5709. <a href=\"https://t.co/83kBMxygOf\">pic.twitter.com/83kBMxygOf</a></p>&mdash; Mansfield Police TX (@MansfieldPDTX) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MansfieldPDTX/status/1313920415589380097?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 7, 2020</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://twitter.com/MansfieldPDTX/status/1313920415589380097",
          "author_name": "Mansfield Police TX",
          "author_url": "https://twitter.com/MansfieldPDTX",
          "width": 550,
          "height": null,
          "cache_age": "3153600000",
          "provider_name": "Twitter",
